    <stitle>SINGLE REDUCTION, TANDEM AXLE: INTERNATIONAL - DESCRIPTION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The International tandem rear axle assemblies consist of two heavy duty, hypoid, single reduction
                carrier assemblies. The forward axle contains a power divider.
            </para>
            <para>The power divider does exactly what its name implies, divides power between the forward rear and rear
                rear axle assemblies. The forward axle receives power via a set of helical gears within the power
                divider.
            </para>
            <para>The rear rear axle receives power from the power divider via an output shaft that extends through the
                forward axle housing.
            </para>
            <para>The complete forward axle carrier assembly and power divider can be removed from the axle housing as a
                unit.
            </para>
            <para>The power divider and inter-axle differential can also be removed from the forward axle without
                disturbing the carrier assembly. This saves valuable time if service to the power divider is all that is
                required.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Inter-axle assembly may be serviced separately without removing complete carrier assembly from
                        vehicle. This is done by removing inter-axle and intermediate case as an assembly from carrier.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
